[_Yersinia pestis_ is the agent responsible for causing bubonic plague.
Endemic foci of sylvatic plague exist in the western USA and several other
areas of the world. Fleas are the vectors primary responsible for
spreading _Y. pestis_ from these reservoirs, although contact with infected
rabbit carcasses has been a significant source of infection for man during
the winter. Throughout history, outbreaks of human plague involving rats in
densely populated agricultural or urban areas have occurred when rats
commingled with infected sylvatic rodents. - Mod.TG
